Install AWS-CDK

---------First Install AWS-CLI on MAC---------
source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BNH4i7CQ4Oc&ab_channel=DennisTraub 

1: Install and update for all users using the macOS command line:
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/AWSCLIV2.pkg" -o AWSCLIV2.pkg
sudo installer -pkg AWSCLIV2.pkg -target /
rm AWSCLIV2.pkg

2: Verify the installation:
$ which aws
/usr/local/bin/aws 
$ aws --version

3: Quick configuration with aws configure:
$ aws configure
AWS Access Key ID [None]: {Acces_Key}
AWS Secret Access Key [None]: {Secret_Key}
Default region name [None]: us-west-2
Default output format [None]: json

4: See which user u connect 
$ aws sts get-caller-identity

------------Install npm on Mac OS--------------
brew -v
brew update
brew install node
node -v
npm -v

------------Install the AWS Cloud Development Kit (AWS CDK) on Mac OS--------------
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v1U_6Dq6wog&ab_channel=DennisTraub
npm install -g aws-cdk
cdk --version


